M a l e: Protarsomeres 1 to 3 moderately widened. Aedeagus (
Figs 101, 102
) 0.49-0.62 mm long, symmetrical, fairly strongly sclerotized. Apical processes of median lobe shorter than basal bulb, inflexed, almost evenly thick, with ventral side sinuate and blunt tip in lateral view, in dorsal view narrowed posterior basal bulb, widest in apical half, with apical margin broadly rounded; articular processes comparatively small, hardly prominent. Parameres narrowed from bases to apical third and evenly wide in apical third in dorsal view, almost evenly wide and straight with curved apical section in lateral view, reaching beyond tip of median lobe. Internal sac without rods or flagellum, with weakly sclerotized, minute denticles.
